He said, "Repent from your sins! For the kingdom of heaven has drawn near."
John is the one of whom the prophet Isaiah spoke. He said, "A voice cries out: 'In the wilderness prepare the way of the Lord, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.'" (Isaiah 40:3)
John's clothes were made of camel hair. He had a leather belt around his waist. His food was locusts and wild honey.
The people came out to him from Jerusalem and all Judea and from the whole region of the Jordan.
When they confessed that they had sinned, John baptized them in the Jordan.
John saw many Pharisees and Sadducees coming to where he was baptizing. He said to them, "You brood of vipers! Who warned you to flee from the wrath to come?
Bear fruits that show you have turned away from your sins.
