Jesus called his twelve disciples to him and gave them authority to drive out evil spirits and to heal every disease and sickness.
Here are the names of the twelve apostles. The first is Simon Peter and his brother Andrew. Then comes James the son of Zebedee and his brother John.
The next are Philip and Bartholomew, also Thomas and Matthew the tax collector. There are two others, James the son of Alphaeus and Thaddaeus.
