Jesus sent these twelve with the following instructions. He said, "Do not go to those who are not Jews." "Do not enter any town of the Samaritans."
But go to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
As you go, proclaim this message: "The kingdom of heaven is near."
Heal the sick. Raise the dead. Cleanse those who have leprosy. Drive out demons. You received without paying; give without being paid.
Do not take with you gold or silver or copper in your belts.
Don't take a bag for the trip. Don't take extra clothes or sandals or walking sticks. The worker should be given what he needs.
When you enter a city or village, look for someone willing to receive you. Stay in that person's home until you leave.
When you enter the house, greet those who live there.
If that house welcomes you, grant it a blessing of peace. If it does not, do not bless it.
Some people may not welcome you or listen to your words. If they don't, shake the dust off your feet when you leave that house or town.
What I am about to tell you is the truth. On the Day of Judgment, the condition of Sodom and Gomorrah will be easier than that of this city.
I am sending you out like sheep among wolves. Therefore be as prudent as serpents and as innocent as doves.
Beware! The men will hand you over to the local courts. They will whip you in their temples.
You will be brought before governors and kings because of me. You will be witnesses to them and to the Gentiles.
But when they arrest you, don't worry about what you will say or how you will say it. At that time, the right words will be given to you.
You will not be the speaker. It is the spirit of your father that will speak through you.
Brothers will hand over their brothers to be killed. Fathers will hand over their children. Children will rise up against their parents and put them to death.
Everyone will hate you because of me. But whoever stands firm to the end will be saved.
When people attack you in one place, flee to another. What I am telling you is true. You will not finish going through the cities of Israel before the Son of Man comes.
The student is not better than his teacher. The servant is not better than his master.
It is enough for the disciple to be like his teacher, and enough for the servant to be like his master. If the head of the house is called Beelzebul, what can those who live there expect?
Do not be afraid of your enemies. Everything that is secret will be revealed. Everything that is hidden will be brought to light.
What I tell you in the dark, speak in the daylight; what is whispered in your ear, shout from the rooftops.
Do not fear those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. Rather, fear him who can destroy both soul and body in hell.
Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? Yet not one of them will fall to the ground outside your Father's care.
He's counting every hair on your head!
So do not fear. You are worth more than many sparrows.
What about someone who says in front of others that he knows me? I too will say in front of my Father in heaven that I know him.
But what about someone who says in front of others that he doesn't know me? I will say in front of my Father in heaven that I don't know him.
Do not think that I have come to bring peace to the earth. I have not come to bring peace, but a sword.
I have come to turn "sons against their fathers, and daughters against their mothers, and daughters-in-law against their mothers-in-law.
"A man's foes shall be they of his own household." (Micah 7:6)
Whoever loves their father or mother more than me is not worthy of me. Whoever loves their son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.
"And whoever does not take up his cross and follow me is not worthy of me."
If anyone finds his life, he will lose it. And if anyone loses his life for my sake, he will find it.
Whoever welcomes you welcomes me, and whoever welcomes me welcomes the one who sent me.
Assume that a person welcomes a prophet as a prophet. That person will receive the reward of a prophet. And assume that a person welcomes a righteous person as a righteous person. That person will receive the reward of a righteous person.
Suppose someone gave a glass of cold water to a child who follows me. What I am about to tell you is true. That person will surely be rewarded.
