It is he who was written about in the Holy Book. It says: "Behold, I will send my messenger, and he will prepare the way before you." (Malachi 3:1)
What I am about to tell you is the truth. No one born of woman is greater than John the Baptist. Yet even the least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.
Since the days of John the Baptist, the kingdom of heaven has been advancing with power. And the violent take it by force.
All the prophets and the law prophesied until John came.
If you are willing to accept it, John is Elijah who was to come.
"Whoever has ears, let them hear."
By what can I compare the people of today? They are like children sitting in the markets, calling out to others. They say,
