But you allow people to say to their parents, "Any help you have received from us is a gift dedicated to God."
They do not need to honor their parents with their gift. You make the word of God of no effect in order to follow your own teachings.
Oh protesters! Isaiah was right when he prophesied about you. He said,
"These people honor me with their words, but their hearts are far from me."
"Their worship means nothing to me. They only know human rules." (Isaiah 29:13)
Jesus called the crowd to him and said, "Listen and understand.
What goes into your mouth does not make you "unclean." What comes out of your mouth is what makes you "unclean."
Then the disciples came to him. They asked, "Do you know that the Pharisees were offended when they heard this?"
