Jesus and his disciples arrived at Capernaum. There, the tax collectors came to Peter and asked, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
"Yes, he does," he replied. When Peter came into the house, Jesus spoke first. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "Who collects taxes from the kings of the earth? Do they collect them from their sons or from others?"
"I am," Peter replied. Jesus said to him, "Then the children are exempt."
But we don't want to anger them. So go to the lake and cast your line. Take the first fish you catch. Open its mouth. There you will find the small coin you need. Take it and give it to them for my tax and yours.
